    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-11-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-11-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="18" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d18">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Tripp</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17,
                                    1893</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No 43.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge receipt of your Nos.
                            50 and 51, of the 29th ultimo and 1st instant, in relation to the claim
                            of Mr. E. W. Mix against the Austrian Government growing out of his
                            arrest on suspicion of being a Russian spy.</p>
                <p>The Department approves your conclusion that upon the facts this
                            Government would not be warranted in making a claim against the Austrian
                            Government on behalf of Mr. Mix for damages. By taking photographs at
                            Przemysl he violated the law in force there, and however innocent in his
                            intentions or ignorant of the law he may have been, his acts subjected
                            him to the arrest and annoyance which he suffered. His release was by
                            your exertions effected as soon as could possibly have been expected,
                            and meantime no harsh or unreasonable treatment seems to have been
                            experienced by him.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
